            "id": "0229adc2b67e4739b0527",
            "questionText": "A student is using an old electric kettle and a toaster simultaneously from a single, visibly damaged extension cord in their dormitory room. The kettle is rated at $!$2200\\,\\text{W}$!$ and the toaster at $!$1000\\,\\text{W}$!$. The mains supply voltage is $!$230\\,\\text{V}$!$. If the resistance of the extension cord is $!$0.5\\,\\Omega$!$, calculate the rate of heat produced by the extension cord.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "c283d408ef5341e5ba829",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the total power demand by adding the power ratings of the kettle and toaster. Compute the sum of $!$2200\\,\\text{W}$!$ and $!$1000\\,\\text{W}$!$.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "3200"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "W",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "8dc73760fc944ea58b345",
                    "stepText": "Great, now that you have the total power, identify the correct formula that relates power, voltage, and current to determine the current drawn from the mains. Which formula should be used?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "9b6731ea-3a10-4320-b77b-a729fcfd2577"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I=\\frac{P}{V}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I=\\frac{V}{P}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I=P\\times V$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$I=\\frac{R}{V}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "2082f82a9be04db09305a",
                    "stepText": "Using the total power calculated and the mains voltage of $!$230\\,\\text{V}$!$, calculate the current drawn. Use the formula you just identified.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "13.91"
