            "questionText": "A homeowner mistakenly connected the neutral wire of a domestic ring main circuit to the switch terminal intended for the live wire while replacing a light switch. Assume that the mains supply voltage is $!$240\\,V$!$ and that the effective impedance between the metallic casing of the light fixture and the earth ground is $!$R\\,\\Omega$!$. If the homeowner accidentally touches the casing when the switch is off, a current will flow through their body. Calculate the magnitude of the current (in amperes) that flows through the homeowner. (Note: If $!$R\\,\\Omega$!$ is not provided, please supply its numerical value.)",
